&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About CueBox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://getcuebox.com/&quot;&gt;CueBox&lt;/a&gt; is a fast-growing early stage startup that offers a modern and all-in-one ticketing, fundraising, CRM software for performing arts organizations. These organizations are vital to local communities, yet, many of their operations are hampered by antiquated technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CueBox’s software directly increases our customers’ revenue (ticketing, donations), improves patron/donor experience and saves time on manual work. Our mission is to empower arts orgs with the best software to deliver the best patron/donor experience and expand their reach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a growing customer base across theaters, symphonies, operas, ballets, choruses, and performing arts centers across the US who love our product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a highly-motivated and entrepreneurial Founding Account Executive to join our growing team. You will be responsible for managing the full sales cycle (lead generation, cold outbound, prospecting, demos, closing deals) and bringing in net new business to drive CueBox’s growth. The ideal candidate is driven, resourceful, tenacious, has a track record of success, and experienced in customer-centric &amp;amp; consultative selling techniques with multiple stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: $100,000-150,000 OTE (50/50), uncapped commission&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to remote candidates based in the US. For NYC, you can come into our office located in the Financial District.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and own the full sales cycle: cold outbound (cold emails, LinkedIn, cold calls), discovery, demo, negotiation and close new customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with the executive decision maker and key influencers (e.g., Fundraising and Marketing Leaders) to drive sales using a consultative and multi-threaded approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customers’ key goals and pain points to conduct effective discovery sessions and present custom demos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate pricing terms to secure agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed records of sales activities and pipeline in CRM tool (Hubspot)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend industry conferences and events to showcase CueBox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate directly with CEO on sales strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with rest of the team to ensure customer success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of full cycle B2B SaaS sales experience, preferably at a fast growing software company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of exceeding sales targets and selling to SMB and mid-market customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to sell into executives (head of organization, head of a department) and work with multiple stakeholders to close deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of outbound prospecting and building your own pipeline through cold emails and cold calls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional discovery, demo and closing skills using a consultative and customer-centric approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, growth-oriented and ability to manage projects independently in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity and genuine interest about our product, mission and industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn and adapt quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s or equivalent degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Bonus) Experience selling software to non-profit organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Bonus) Personal arts/music-related experience or interest&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Additional Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Founding Business Development Representative&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: $80,000-90,000 OTE ($50,000-60,000 base), uncapped commission&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About CueBox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://getcuebox.com/&quot;&gt;CueBox&lt;/a&gt; is a fast-growing startup building a modern, all-in-one ticketing, fundraising, and marketing CRM software for performing arts organizations. Theaters, symphonies, operas, ballets, choruses, and performing arts centers are vital to their communities — but most are stuck running on antiquated technology that gets in the way of doing their best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CueBox changes that. Our software directly grows our customers&#39; revenue (ticketing and donations), improves the patron and donor experience, and gives staff their time back from manual work. We have a growing customer base across the US who genuinely love the product, and we&#39;re looking to expand the team that gets CueBox in front of more arts organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CueBox works with orgs across the US including El Paso Symphony, HERE Arts Center in NYC and more. One of the music orgs that CueBox works with increased ticket sales by &amp;gt;30% and ticket donations by 5x in several months after switching over to CueBox.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring our founding business development representatives (BDRs) to drive the top of our sales funnel. You&#39;ll own outbound prospecting into performing arts organizations across the US — building lists, running multi-channel outreach, qualifying inbound leads, and booking discovery calls for our sales team. &lt;strong&gt;This is a high-impact role at a small and fast-moving company: your work directly shapes pipeline and revenue, you’ll partner directly with our CEO/co-founder, and you&#39;ll have the opportunity to grow into an account executive role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: $80,000-90,000 OTE ($50,000-60,000 base), uncapped commission&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location (Remote)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to remote candidates based in the US. We do have an office in NYC that you can optionally come into some days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run outbound prospecting campaigns (cold emails, calls, LinkedIn outreaches) into performing arts organizations
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously test and improve outreach: subject lines, sequences, talk tracks and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build outbound prospecting lists by using a range of different sources (including industry lists, industry database, online web research, sales tools) for cold outreach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research target accounts and personalize outreach to the executive decision makers and key influencers (fundraising, marketing, box office)
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customers’ key goals and pain points to conduct effective initial cold calls and write relevant outbound messages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Book discovery meetings for the sales team, with clean handoffs and context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate, up-to-date records in our CRM and sales engagement tools (Hubspot)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hit and exceed monthly activity and meeting targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend industry conferences and events to showcase CueBox&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share what you&#39;re hearing from prospects with leadership — your feedback will shape our roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–2+ years of BDR/SDR experience in B2B software sales, with a track record of hitting or exceeding quota&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
