&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About CueBox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CueBox is an early-stage startup building all-in-one software for performing arts and cultural organizations. These organizations inspire, connect and delight us; yet, they’ve been underserved by technology providers. Our product saves them time and grows their revenue by streamlining fundraising, ticketing, marketing, education and more, which is why we have such a fast-growing and happy customer base!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are quickly expanding into more segments across the country, and we’re looking for a talented and driven engineer to help our small team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CueBox is headquartered in New York City, and we are a hybrid workplace. Our team is in the office 3 days a week, Tuesday–Thursday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for backend-leaning full-stack engineers who love building delightful and performant products, are excited to work hard at a mission-oriented startup, and want to collaborate with us in shaping the culture of a growing team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4+ years of professional software engineering experience&lt;/strong&gt;, including prior experience at an early or mid stage startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bachelor’s degree or higher in Computer Science or a related technical field&lt;/strong&gt; (or equivalent practical experience).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven track record of building performant, data-intensive applications using a strongly typed backend language&lt;/strong&gt; in a complex domain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product sense and high customer empathy; genuine desire to build the best possible product for our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excels at thoughtful API design and database schema/query design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with integrating Backend APIs with a TypeScript/React frontend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and successfully own large or ambiguous problem areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective verbal and written communication for both technical and nontechnical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with online payments, consumer facing flows, or reporting/analytics for large datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Nice-to-Have) Experience building AI-enabled features in SaaS products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role reports directly to the Head of Engineering. You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, maintain and scale our backend systems as we grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pioneer new features and product areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meaningfully influence technical direction as the product evolves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a culture of engineering excellence through technical design discussion, code review, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in our current tech stack: Golang/Protobuf/Postgres backend; React/Next.js/Chakra UI frontend; Python data pipelines; hosted on GCP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current and Upcoming Projects include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building brand new products such as educational/youth-programming modules and data-driven pricing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improving performance, user experience and accessibility of consumer-facing checkout flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scaling up and rearchitecting our backend systems to handle more user traffic and heavier analytics workloads.&lt;/li&gt;
